############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Suppose we want to see if an exam prep program will affect students’ performance on the Calculus I gateway exam (a test that students can take multiple times until they pass it). We obtain a random sample of Calculus I students and record their scores on the gateway exam before and after they participate in the exam prep program. Choose the appropriate test.
[_]{$mc}{5}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION The study involves two dependent samples with matched data \- before and after results for individuals were recorded. This means the Paired T-Test is the appropriate test to use. END_PGML_SOLUTION
